trans-unit.source: Create, plan, and execute tasks in project management.
trans-unit.note: Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action2 - Property ToolTip
Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action2 - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: Open the list of ongoing job tasks. Job tasks represent the actual work that is performed in a job, and they enable you to set up job planning lines and to post consumption to the job.
trans-unit.note: Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action3 - Property ToolTip
Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action3 - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: Define a project activity by creating a job card with integrated job tasks and job planning lines, structured in two layers. The job task enables you to set up job planning lines and to post consumption to the job. The job planning lines specify the detailed use of resources, items, and various general ledger expenses.
trans-unit.note: Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action90 - Property ToolTip
Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action90 - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: Open the list of ongoing job planning lines for the job. You use this window to plan what items, resources, and general ledger expenses that you expect to use on a job (budget) or you can specify what you actually agreed with your customer that he should pay for the job (billable).
trans-unit.note: Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Job Planning Lines - Property ToolTip
Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Job Planning Lines - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: Record job expenses or usage in the job ledger, either by reusing job planning lines or by manual entry.

trans-unit.note: Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action91 - Property ToolTip
Page IMP Job Project Manager RC - Action Action91 - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: Manage your resources' job activities by setting up their costs and prices. The job-related prices, discounts, and cost factor rules are set up on the respective job card. You can specify the costs and prices for individual resources, resource groups, or all available resources of the company. When resources are used or sold in a job, the specified prices and costs are recorded for the project.
